<br>
I'd advise that opponent's hits and misses stay on, at least for casters for spell timing...hard to get a spell off if you can't see that you're being hit or at least swung at...just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
Point being...the text can fly by and you can miss stuff...but you'd only need to say it two times at most if anyone is paying attention...that's sort of the idea of the eyes up line of text...to let people know stuff is coming...that way you should only have to say it once.<br>
<br>
If the Enforcer can get people trained to listening to him/her first...or recognizing the name for a set of commands, then the Raid Organizers can get their stuff in once the Enforcer calls them to attention...that's kinda the route I'd take it anyway. <p>Good Journies,<BR>
